<Base title="APFS-RS Quality Evidence">
  <h1>Quality evidence</h1>
  <p>The quality evidence ledger separates configured checks from executed checks so handoff status remains honest.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Required CI runs format, clippy, tests, dynamic version output, context checks, safety checks, version consistency, profiling audits, release automation audit, and the aggregate bleeding-edge audit.</li>
    <li>Scheduled profiling runs Criterion benchmarks for <code>apfs-core</code> and <code>apfs-types</code>.</li>
    <li>Release automation invokes cargo-dist planning and release-plz local update checks with publishing disabled until MVP gates are accepted.</li>
    <li>Renovate maintains Cargo, GitHub Actions, npm, Dockerfile, and Python requirement dependencies, with policy review required for risky crypto/TLS transitive dependency updates.</li>
  </ul>
</Base>
